			News file for CCTests
			=====================

Revision 0.4.0-devel.0
----------------------

* Added assertions:

     cctests_assert_true()
     cctests_assert_false()

* Added   optional   arguments    to   format   an   assertion-violation
  description-message to the assertion macros.

* BACKWARDS  INCOMPATIBILITY   Added  an   argument  assertion-violation
  description-message  to   the  constructors  of   assertion  condition
  objects.

* Added counters for tests.

* Better support for terminal colours.


Revision 0.3.0-devel.7
----------------------

* Package infrastructure development.


Revision 0.3.0-devel.6
----------------------

* Package infrastructure development.

* Added some printing facilities for debugging purposes.

* Extended  "cctests_condition_assertion_t"  to   include  an  optional,
  dynamically allocated, string as description message.

* Added macro "cctests_assert_msg()" to  include a formatted description
  message in the raised exceptional-condition object.


Revision 0.3.0-devel.5
----------------------

* Package infrastructure development.


Revision 0.3.0-devel.4
----------------------

* Miscellaneous fixes.


Revision 0.3.0-devel.3
----------------------

* Development of build infrastructure.


Revision 0.3.0-devel.2
----------------------


* Updated to CCExceptions v0.8.0-devel.4.

* Added missing C header includes.


Revision 0.3.0-devel.1
----------------------

* Updated code to CCExceptions revision 0.8.0-devel.3.


Revision 0.3.0-devel.0
----------------------

* Updated code to CCExceptions revision 0.8.0-devel.2.

* Removed useless system function interfaces.


Revision 0.2.0-devel.4
----------------------

* Fixed data script for "pkg-config".


Revision 0.2.0-devel.3
----------------------

* Added correct "printf()" format codes for "size_t".


Revision 0.2.0-devel.2
----------------------

* Updated to CCExceptions 0.8.0.


Revision 0.2.0-devel.1
----------------------

* More documentation.

* More equality assertions: pointers.


Revision 0.2.0-devel.0
----------------------

* Updated to CCExceptions version 0.7.2.


Revision 0.1.0-devel.1
----------------------

* Added assertion functions for expected values.

* Added condition object types for assertions.

* Added colourisation of output when the output device is a terminal.

* Added support for "cctests_condition_skipped_t".

* Fixed version in pkg-config file.


Revision 0.1.0-devel.0
----------------------

* Initial development release.


